Which file regards: strings_lists_chars.s

So basically in this code we have two kinds of data in section .data:
  char   DB 'A'                        ; single character value
  list   DB 1,2,3,4,-1                 ; numeric list ended by -1 marker
  string DB "asm is c but harder",0   ; C-like string ended by 0 byte

In section .text we set entry point:

_start:                               ; program start point (entry)
    xor ebx, ebx                      ; clear EBX (set to 0)
    mov bl, [char]                    ; load char value ('A'=65) into BL lower byte of EBX

    mov eax, 1                        ; sys_exit syscall number (Linux i386)
    int 80h                           ; call kernel

Why is list and string defined but not used? educational sample:
- list is an example of using an end-marker (-1) to terminate arrays in ASM
- string is a null terminated byte sequence like C-strings
- they’re not on path to syscall here, but you can print them by sys_write (EAX=4, EBX=1, ECX=string, EDX=len)

Extra notes:
- `DB` = define byte (allocate data and optional initialization)
- `section .data` is for initialized static data and constants
- `section .text` is for executable code
- if you want to use string/list values later, use `mov ecx, string` (address in ECX) and `mov edx, <length>` before sys_write

